{"title_page": "Nimra Khan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2017}}\n{{COI|date=May 2017}}\n}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name = Nimra Khan\n| image = https://www.google.com.pk/search?q=nimra+khan&client=ucweb-lite-b&channel=sb&prmd=ibnv&sxsrf=ALeKk01vVAtIppZYnbThWQw0tg3iGcf7jg:1586290730208&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwig1u-7kdfoAhUCDmMBHTnICv4Q_AUoAXoECA8QAQ&biw=360&bih=518#imgrc=unYW8MGG0Rq9GM\n| caption = Khan at an event in 2018\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|6|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Karachi]], Pakistan\n| nationality = Pakistani\n| occupation = Actress\n| image_size = Karachi\n| residence = \n}}\n'''Nimra Khan''' (Urdu: \u0646\u0645\u0631\u06c1 \u062e\u0627\u0646) (born 26 June 1990) is a Pakistani model, actress and director.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pakistani.pk/nimrah-khan/|title=Nimrah Khan Drama List, Height, Date of Birth & Net Worth|website=Pakistani.PK - Your Local Guide to Business Listings, Restaurants, Hotels &amp; Product Reviews|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-23}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nNimra Khan was born on 26 June 1990 in [[Karachi]], her home town. She possess both Pakistan as well as British nationality. Nimra completed her secondary education in Karachi and received a graduation degree in Film Making from the famous Arts school IVS ([[Indus Valley School of Art and Architecture]]). She had also received a certificate in acting. She operates her own beauty salon as she strongly believes in women empowerment. She is also a good squash player.\n\nOn 21 August 2014 she was seriously injured in a road accident. Her car got hit badly by a van while she was coming back from her shoot. Her right leg fractured from five different points. Doctors were not able to fix them immediately as there were a few clots in her brain.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://aaj.tv/2014/08/pakistani-actress-nimra-khan-seriously-injured-in-a-ccar-accident/|title=Pakistani actress Nimra Khan seriously injured in a car accident|work=Aaj News|access-date=2017-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://arynews.tv/en/pakistani-celebrities-who-met-horrible-road-accidents/|title=Pakistani celebrities who met horrible road accidents!|date=2016-08-01|work=ARYNEWS|access-date=2017-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n=== Television ===\nShe played a lead role in her debut television play Khwaab Tabeer on [[Pakistan Television Corporation|PTV]]. She is known for her performances in Kaisi Khushi Lekar Aaya Chand on A-Plus, opposite [[Ahsan Khan (actor)|Ahsan Khan]], Rishta Anjana Sa on [[ARY Digital|Ary Digital]] and [[Choti Si Zindagi]] on Hum TV.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1150493|title=Shehzad Sheikh is back with Choti Si Zindagi and three more projects|date=2016-08-16|work=HIP|access-date=2017-03-29|language=en}}</ref> In 2019, she had a good year as she was praised for her performances in the smash-hit drama [[Bhool (2019 TV series)|Bhool]] on [[ARY Digital]] and popular hit series Uraan on [[A-Plus TV|A-Plus]].\n\n=== Films ===\nHer debut film was [[Blind Love (2015 film)|Blind Love]] in which she played the lead role of the blind woman Sara.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1109362/upcoming-blind-love-hit-theatres-come-eid/|title=Upcoming: \u2018Blind Love\u2019 to hit theatres come Eid - The Express Tribune|date=2016-05-24|work=The Express Tribune|access-date=2017-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref> She appeared as Hayya in [[Saya e Khuda e Zuljalal]], an action-war film about the Pakistan independence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1196314|title=Saya-e-Khuda-e-Zuljalal is not just another war movie, say the producers|date=2015-07-25|work=DAWN.COM|access-date=2017-03-29|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Films ==\n* ''[[Blind Love (2016 film)|Blind Love]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Saya e Khuda e Zuljalal]]'' (2016)\n\n== Television ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Serial\n!Movies / Drama\n!Role\n!Channel\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2013\n|Chubhan\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Pakistan Television Corporation|PTV]]\n|-\n|Zard E Chaon\n|Drama\n|\n|[[TVOne Pakistan|TV One]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2014\n|Khawab Tabeer\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Pakistan Television Corporation|PTV]]\n|-\n|[[Shareek-e-Hayat]]\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Hum TV]]\n|-\n|Pehli Jumeraat\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Express Entertainment]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2015\n|Chhoti Si Ghalat Fehmi\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Hum TV]]\n|-\n|[[Mere Khuda]]\n|Drama\n|Saba\n|[[Hum TV]]\n|-\n|rowspan=5|2016\n|Mere Humdum\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Aaj Entertainment]]\n|-\n|[[Jab We Wed]]\n|Drama\n|Rumi\n|[[Urdu 1]]\n|-\n|Kaisi Khushi Le ke Aya Chand\n|Drama\n|\n|[[A-Plus TV|A-Plus]]\n|-\n|Rishta Anjana Sa\n|Drama\n|\n|[[Ary Digital]]\n|-\n|''[[Choti Si Zindagi]]''\n|Drama\n|Azra\n|[[Hum TV]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2017\n|''[[Baaghi (TV series)|Baaghi]]''\n|Drama\n|Munni\n|[[Urdu 1]]\n|-\n|''[[Alif Allah Aur Insaan]]''\n|Drama\n|Zimmal\n|[[Hum TV]]\n|-\n|''[[Meherbaan (drama)|Meherbaan]]''\n|Drama\n|Dua\n|[[A-Plus TV|A-Plus]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2019\n|Uraan\n|Drama\n|\n|[[A-Plus TV|A-Plus]]\n|-\n|[[Daag (TV series)|Bhool]]\n|Drama\n|Sidra\n|[[ARY Digital]]\n|-\n|Main Jeena Chahthi Hoon\n|Drama\n|Sidra\n|[[PTV Home]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Refbegin}}\n:* [http://www.awamiweb.com/actress-nimra-khan-new-face-pakistani-showbiz-71967.html Actress Nimra Khan \u2013 A New Face in Pakistani Showbiz]\n:* [https://fashion360.pk/beautiful-and-talented-actress-nimra-khan-got-engaged/ Beautiful and Talented Actress Nimra Khan got Engaged]\n:* [http://reviewit.pk/nimra-khans-first-interview-after-her-accident/ Nimra Khan\u2019s First Interview After Her Accident]\n:* [http://he99.blogspot.com/2014/10/actress-nimra-khans-survival-journey.html Actress Nimra Khan's survival Journey after very badly accident Back to the life]\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|8030287}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Nimra}}\n[[Category:21st-century Pakistani actresses]]\n[[Category:Pakistani femal